The extension is .ps1

To allow powershell scripts to run in your pc

in powershell as administrator run:

Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned

Tipe "A" and then press Enter!

Now you can run you .ps1 files!

To write scripts you can also use PowerShell ISE


________________
in cmd extension is usually .bat

to stop the script press ctrl+c and type 'Y'

If you press up arrow and down arrow command history will work!

in cmd you can also leave some rows empty. nothing will happen
and the code will be more tidy.
